cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep neural network-based model for multi-label classification, which is a common task in machine learning related fields. The paper focuses on joint feature and label embedding, which is a key aspect of deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of label-correlation sensitive loss function, which is relevant to natural language processing tasks, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. Finally, the use of autoencoder architecture suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category.
